article.headline: Northern Iowa 64, Evansville 61
article.story: CEDAR FALLS, Iowa (AP) -- Grant Stout matched his season high with 17 points and Adam Viet added 11 to lead Northern Iowa past Evansville 64-61. Evansville trailed by as much as 15 midway through the second half, but Jason Holsinger's 3-pointer with 38 seconds left pulled the Aces within 61-59. Northern Iowa's Travis Brown hit two free throws, and Shy Ely answered with a layup to bring the Aces back within two. But Evansville was called for an intentional foul on an inbounds pass with 1.2 seconds left, sealing the win for the Panthers. Brown chipped in with 10 points for Northern Iowa (12-2, 3-0 Missouri Valley), which is 10-1 since losing to No. 24 Washington last month. The Panthers pushed a seven-point halftime lead to 52-37 midway through the second half. Brown followed four Stout free throws with a jumper, and Stout hit a layup on the Panthers' next possession to give Northern Iowa its largest lead. Evansville (9-6, 2-2) answered with an 13-1 run, highlighted by layups from Shy and Bradley Strickland and a 3-pointer from Art Stalbergs. Stalbergs and Matt Webster each had 12 to lead the Aces. Stout became the 29th player in Northern Iowa history to pass the 1,000-point mark with a basket in the first half.
